      "writtenOn": "2018-11-20T15:36:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Personally I like the modifies at the end, but I\u0027m happy to default to whatever.\n\nGenerally my thought process with naming is if I want to compare two timings that should have some commonality in the start of their name. So in this case if you want to compare local coord to non local coord, I think both benches should start with the same name. If you don\u0027t ever care to compare them, then it doesn\u0027t matter. So in the end I would decide is local coords just modifying the rect bench, or do I want to treat it as its own thing.",
      "parentUuid": "6e13854e_1e0bd3d1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 184,
